    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">ShortAnswerResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>One batch of cookies calls for 1 bag of mix and the ingredients shown in the table.</p>

<table border="1">
	<thead>
		<tr>
			<th scope="row">type of cookie</th>
			<th scope="col">eggs</th>
			<th scope="col">water</th>
			<th scope="col">oil</th>
		</tr>
	</thead>
	<tbody>
		<tr>
			<th scope="row">regular</th>
			<td>1 egg</td>
			<td><span><span><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mfrac>
    <mn>1</mn>
    <mn>8</mn>
  </mfrac>
</math></span><annotation description="\(\frac18\)"></annotation></span></td>
			<td><span><span><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mfrac>
    <mn>1</mn>
    <mn>3</mn>
  </mfrac>
</math></span><annotation description="\(\frac13\)"></annotation></span></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<th scope="row">cake-like</th>
			<td>2 eggs</td>
			<td><span><span><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mfrac>
    <mn>1</mn>
    <mn>8</mn>
  </mfrac>
</math></span><annotation description="\(\frac18\)"></annotation></span></td>
			<td><span><span><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mfrac>
    <mn>1</mn>
    <mn>3</mn>
  </mfrac>
</math></span><annotation description="\(\frac13\)"></annotation></span></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody>
</table>

<ol>
	<li>
	<p>What amounts of eggs, water, and oil would you need for 2 batches of regular cookies?<presentation-tag src="/presentation_tags/4.tag"></presentation-tag><presentation-tag src="/presentation_tags/4.tag"></presentation-tag></p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p>What amounts of eggs, water, and oil would you need for 3 batches of cake-like cookies?<presentation-tag src="/presentation_tags/4.tag"></presentation-tag><presentation-tag src="/presentation_tags/4.tag"></presentation-tag></p>
	</li>
</ol>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><ol>
	<li>2 eggs, <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="451">\(\frac{1}{4}\)</span> cup water, <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="403">\(\frac{2}{3}\)</span> cup oil (or equivalent)</li>
	<li>6 eggs, <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="396">\(\frac{3}{8}\)</span> cup water, 1 cup oil (or equivalent)</li>
</ol>
</div>
